@node _fcntl_r
@section @code{_fcntl_r}---Reentrant version of fcntl
@findex _fcntl_r
@strong{Synopsis}
@example
#include <reent.h>
int _fcntl_r(struct _reent *@var{ptr},
    int @var{fd}, int @var{cmd}, @var{arg});

@end example
@strong{Description}@*
This is a reentrant version of @code{fcntl}.  It
takes a pointer to the global data block, which holds
@code{errno}.

@*
